{"TopicId":208831,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"suborbital tug","CreatedByName":"imcute","CreatedById":221897,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-04T00:40:46Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"imcute","CreatedById":221897,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-04T00:40:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwould adding a plane module to every atmosphered celestial body to tug passing rockets save fuel and pardon the nervae?(james kerman did not like nervae due to not working in atmosphere or with intakes)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"king of nowhere","CreatedById":204876,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-04T05:33:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nso, you are thinking that a passing rocket would pass into the atmosphere, and there you would meet it with a plane and give it a push?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ngood luck trying. rendez-vous inside an atmosphere with an object on an escape trajectory. maybe someone could pull off that challenge, but i don\u0027t want to even try.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"imcute","CreatedById":221897,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-04T05:36:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224151397\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022208831\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221656912813\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022204876\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022king of nowhere\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, king of nowhere said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nso, you are thinking that a passing rocket would pass into the atmosphere, and there you would meet it with a plane and give it a push?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nno\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ni mean that a plane should be on the ground and a rocket should land and dock onto it and the plane should push the rocket into suborbital trajectory and land safetly\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"king of nowhere","CreatedById":204876,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-04T06:26:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthen I still say it\u0027s horribly inefficient.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ndo that rocket need to land? then it\u0027s landed, done.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ndo that rocket need to move to another planet? then do an orbital refueling, no need to land the rocket.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI just can\u0027t see any scenario where landing a rocket from orbit on a plane that will send it to orbit again would be useful.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"imcute","CreatedById":221897,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-04T06:43:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\noh\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"imcute","CreatedById":221897,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-04T07:03:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224151413\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022208831\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221656915968\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022204876\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022king of nowhere\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n34 minutes ago, king of nowhere said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ndo that rocket need to land? then it\u0027s landed, done.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\noh wait i meant that it is landed and it needs a plane to take off and refuel\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nnot using the plane to make it land\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Zacspace","CreatedById":188888,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-06T01:01:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224151413\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022208831\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221656915968\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022204876\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022king of nowhere\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 7/4/2022 at 2:26 AM, king of nowhere said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI just can\u0027t see any scenario where landing a rocket from orbit on a plane that will send it to orbit again would be useful.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think they\u0027re going for a reusable flyback booster type thing, just with the booster being on another planet.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224151426\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022208831\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221656918195\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022221897\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022imcute\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 7/4/2022 at 3:03 AM, imcute said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\noh wait i meant that it is landed and it needs a plane to take off and refuel\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s doable. I\u0027ve seen it done from Kerbin at least. It\u0027s hard to make it work without KSP deleting one craft or the other though, since you can only fly one at a time.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nProbably the more KSP friendly version of this would be to use a conventional heavy-lift \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E to bring a nerv or ion powered spacecraft to low orbit and then then release it, landing the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E after.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"imcute","CreatedById":221897,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-06T01:56:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224152015\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022208831\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221657069292\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022188888\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Zacspace\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n48 minutes ago, Zacspace said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthink they\u0027re going for a reusable flyback booster type thing,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nyes\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224152015\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022208831\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221657069292\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022188888\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Zacspace\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n48 minutes ago, Zacspace said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n, just with the booster being on another planet.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nits also okay on kerbin\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(yes i would really like something like that on tylo)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224152015\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022208831\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221657069292\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022188888\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Zacspace\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n49 minutes ago, Zacspace said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nto low orbit\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ngo to a place like 70km ap and 0km pe(low \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Angle of Attack\u0022\u003Eaoa\u003C/abbr\u003E \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003Essto\u003C/abbr\u003E)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nrelease nerv payload\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\na small push by nerv(to orbit!)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nquickly [ and fly that booster/sstso back and to \u003Cabbr title=\u0022In-Situ Resource Utilization\u0022\u003Eisru\u003C/abbr\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Zacspace","CreatedById":188888,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-06T03:08:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224152028\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022208831\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221657072582\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022221897\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022imcute\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, imcute said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ngo to a place like 70km ap and 0km pe(low \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Angle of Attack\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Angle of Attack\u0022\u003Eaoa\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003Essto\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nrelease nerv payload\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\na small push by nerv(to orbit!)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nquickly [ and fly that booster/sstso back and to \u003Cabbr title=\u0022In-Situ Resource Utilization\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022In-Situ Resource Utilization\u0022\u003Eisru\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe problem with that is that you need to be in control of your plane as it lands or KSP will just delete it and say it crashed, meanwhile you also need to be in control of your spacecraft as it burns to orbit, or else it\u0027ll just fall back into the atmosphere and suffer the same fate as your plane. There are ways to do it, of course, but it\u0027s more trouble than it\u0027s worth if you\u0027re just looking to improve efficiency.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"imcute","CreatedById":221897,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-07-06T03:29:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224152037\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022208831\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221657076880\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022188888\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Zacspace\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n18 minutes ago, Zacspace said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthat you need to be in control of your plane as it lands or KSP will just delete it and say it crashed, meanwhile you also need to be in control of your spacecraft as it burns to orbit,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nif u just need ten seconds to release payload and accelerate to orbit ull catch on the plane and avoid boooooooom\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}